The Jubilee Governor Nominee for Nyandarua County Francis Kimemia received a campaign boost on Tuesday after he was crowned patron for the Nyandarua County Pastors&nbsp;Inter-denominational Networking Team. The former Secretary to the Cabinet was unanimously appointed to the position by pastors from various churches who urged him to steer and unite the team ahead of the August 8 general elections. Kimemia, an ardent catholic and a&nbsp;former seminarian vowed to unite all religious communities in the county. &ldquo; I will ensure an ethical County and Inter-religions community that is founded and propelled by the love and fear of God, a culture of Ethics, shared core values and discipline, exemplary service to society and support religious, legal and secular Institutions,&rdquo; said Kimemia